    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-02-06T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-02-06T14:00:00-05:00" n="204"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d204">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">822.24/459: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Nester</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Quito</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-02-06T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 6, 1943—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 10:02 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>105. For Parkhurst, Board of Economic Warfare, from Wilkinson.<note n="87"
                        xml:id="d204fn87">George V. Parkhurst and H. A. Wilkinson, officials of the
                        Board of Economic Warfare.</note> Embassy advises Decentralization Plan<note
                        n="88" xml:id="d204fn88">Decentralization Plan A; for an outline of the
                        plan, see circular airgram of January 19, 8 p.m., <ref target="#pg_106">p.
                            106</ref>.</note> will be instituted in Ecuador March 1. The Country
                    Agency here will be prepared to start issuing Import Recommendations in
                    accordance with plan of procedure on that date.</p>
                <p>Please advise Embassy of the following: <list>
                        <label>(1)</label>
                        <item>Time schedule to be followed.</item>
                        <label>(2)</label>
                        <item>Target shipping tonnage to be used.</item>
                        <label>(3)</label>
                        <item>A recapitulation of the commodity estimates to be used as
                            targets.</item>
                        <label>(4)</label>
                        <item>A clear statement of the portion of the shipping estimate and each
                            commodity estimate to be set aside for projects.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>Materials lists for all projects approved should be sent as soon as possible.
                    [Wilkinson.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Nester</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
